FBIS3-28618 "dreas027_c_94009" FBIS-EAS-94-027 Document Type:Daily Report 9 Feb 1994 North Korea Koreans in Japan Form Human Rights Association SK0902105594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1026 GMT 9 Feb 94 SK0902105594 Pyongyang KCNA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Tokyo, February 7 (KNS-KCNA) -- The inaugural meeting of the Human Rights Association of Koreans in Japan took place here on February 5. Ho Chong-man, chief vice-chairman of the Central Standing Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongnyon), made a congratulatory speech at the meeting. He said the formation of the association was of great significance not only in upholding the great leader Generalissimo Kim Il-song and the dear leader Marshal Kim Chong-il with loyalty and defending and exalting the anthropocentric socialist homeland of chuche but also in developing the patriotic movement of Chongnyon to defend and expand the rights and life of Koreans in Japan by bringing together their legal and economic knowhow and technologies. Solidarity greetings were made by Japanese figures who were present at the meeting as observers. A letter to Generalissimo Kim Il-song was adopted at the meeting.
